itemDescription: religious leader and emigrant to Plymouth Colony, North America (1566-1644)

wikipedia_page.main: William Brewster (1568 – 10 April 1644) was an English official and Mayflower passenger in 1620. In Plymouth Colony, by virtue of his education and existing stature with those immigrating from the Netherlands, Brewster, a Brownist (or Puritan Separatist), became senior elder and the leader of the community.
